    "causal_summary": "The live sk-code benchmark (phase 010) showed strong routing (D1-intra 92, D2 87, surfaces correct 3/3) but two weak dimensions with converging evidence: D3 efficiency 42 (the model loads ~16-20 resources where the gold is ~5-8) and D4 usefulness about 49 (skill-on beat skill-off on a domain-pattern task but lost on a routine language refactor). Both point at the same behavior: sk-code loads a broad resource slice, which pays off when a domain pattern matters and adds noise on simple tasks.",
